tegory:Marvel Comics LGBT superheroes]]\n[[Category:Marvel Comics LGBT supervillains]]\n[[Category:Marvel Comics titles]]\n[[Category:Marvel vs. Capcom fighters]]\n[[Category:Metafictional characters]]\n[[Category:Self-reflexive comics]]\n[[Category:Superhero film characters]]\n[[Category:Superheroes with alter egos]]\n[[Category:Fictional LGBT characters in film]]\n[[Category:Fictional Canadian people]]\n[[Category:X-Men supporting characters]]\n", "text_old": "{{Merge from|Wade Wilson (film character)|discuss=Talk:Deadpool#Merger Discussion|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=January 2019}}\n{{about||the film based on the character|Deadpool (film)|the video game based on the character|Deadpool (video game)|other uses|Dead pool (disambiguation)}}\n{{short description|Character appearing in Marvel Comics}}\n{{Infobox comics character and title\n<!--Wikipedia:WikiProject Comics-->\n| character_name = Deadpool\n| image          = Deadpool.png\n| caption        = Derived variant cover art of ''Deadpool'' #1 (June 2018) by [[Rob Liefeld]]\n| publisher      = [[Marvel Comics]]\n| debut          = ''[[The New Mutants]]'' #98 (February 1991)\n| creators       = [[Fabian Nicieza]]<br />[[Rob Liefeld]]\n| alter_ego      = Wade Winston Wilson<ref>''Cable & Deadpool'' #36 (April 2007).</ref>\n| species        = Human mutate<ref>''Cable & Deadpool'' #9</ref>\n| alliances      = [[Agent X (Marvel Comics)|Agency X]] <br />[[List of Avengers members#Astonishing Avengers (2014)|Astonishing Avengers]]<br/>[[Uncanny Avengers|Avengers Unity Division]]<br/>Code Red<ref>''Hulk'' vol. 2, #14.</ref> <br/>[[Deadpool Corps]] <br />[[Frightful Four]] <br />[[Great Lakes Avengers|Great Lakes Initiative]] <br />[[Heroes for Hire]] <br />[[Landau, Luckman, and Lake]] <br />[[Maggia (comics)|Maggia]] <br/>[[Mercs for Money]]<ref>''Deadpool'' Vol. 4 #3</ref><br/>[[Defenders (comics)|Secret Defenders]]<br/>[[S.H.I.E.L.D.]] <br/>[[Six Pack (comics)|Six Pack]]<br/>[[Thunderbolts (comics)|Thunder